children.subject: Assuming you are EECS: One possible consequence of leaving physics 7b until past your first 2 years here is that during your 5th semester, you may have an enrollment block imposed upon you for Phase 1 for every semester until you finish the requirement. This is because 7b is technically a lower div. This actually happened to me this semester -- I kept putting off 7b in favor of tech classes, and when I'd fulfilled all of my other major requirements (except 7b), the hold was imposed because I was no longer fulfilling the 2 major requirements / semester (even if I was taking 2 EECS techs this semester). This is just a personal experience, but if you're planning on leaving 7b until your last semester, you might want to consider planning out your schedule really, really carefully to make sure you're fulfilling 2 reqs / sem so you still get the Phase 1 planned for you (otherwise, it's delayed a week afaik).
